description: Gated, private and completely secure, C1901 'Maltoende' rests in a dress-circle pocket on a rare 2600sqm.
This stunning, grand and substantial Federation, has been carefully preserved and sympathetically extended.
The estate-like home sits amidst beautiful manicured gardens with a north/south tennis court and pool.
Interiors are rich in period features and boast sprawling rooms that extend to decks, terraces and balconies.
The country inspired kitchen will win hearts with its vintage style, marble island and commercial grade cooker.
The residence boasts an expansive family room, formal dining, casual dining, home office/gym and a studio.
Perfect for large families, bedrooms are spacious and bright including the master with ensuite, WIR and balcony.
A versatile self-contained wing with kitchenette and balcony makes a perfect rumpus or guest retreat.
Extras include a workshop, abundant storage, powder room and internal access double garage.
From its tranquil surrounds its steps to the bus, rail, village, Wahroonga Public, Abbotsleigh and Knox Grammar School.
headline: 'Maltoende', one of Sydney's finest Federation estates
